<TITLE> OPEC heads of state summit in Riyadh </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Nov 12 (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - Saudi Arabia is hosting the third summit for heads of state of the 12 members of the Organization of the Petroleum Exporting Countries (OPEC) this week in Riyadh. (For a preview click on [ID:L08696237]). Following is information on the summit. - OPEC oil ministers are due to meet informally at a ministerial symposium taking place on Nov. 15-16. The symposium features a number of sessions with ministers participating in panel discussions on energy-related topics. - The gathering in Riyadh lacks the status of a full-blown consultative meeting at which the group's oil ministers take formal decisions on oil output. - Finance and foreign ministers from member states are also expected to be in the delegations to Riyadh. - The heads of states of each of the 12 member countries, plus incoming member Ecuador, are due to meet on Nov. 17-18. Heads of state are not expected to make any coordinated policy decisions at the event. - OPEC's 12 members are Algeria, Angola, Indonesia, Iran, Iraq, Kuwait, Libya, Nigeria, Qatar, Saudi Arabia, United Arab Emirates, and Venezuela. Ecuador plans to rejoin the producer group at the summit. - The first OPEC heads of state summit was held in Algiers, Algeria in March 1975. - The second was held in Caracas, Venezuela in September 20
